1 the recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic
2 Relief Funding on May 12, 2025.
3 SECTION 2. REAPPROPRIATION AND REDESIGNATION
4 The amount of Sixty-six Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars
5 ($66,500,000.00) of the original appropriation of Eighty-seven
6 Million Dollars ($87,000,000.00), appropriated to the Department of
7 Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services by Section 1 of Enrolled
8 House Bill No. 1013 of the 2nd Extraordinary Session of the 58th
9 Oklahoma Legislature, from any monies not otherwise appropriated
10 from the Statewide Recovery Fund of the State Treasury created in
11 Section 255 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, to address the
12 ongoing increased demand for mental health services by constructing
13 a replacement facility for Griffin Memorial Hospital, provided that
14 such construction be confined within a thirty-mile radius of the
15 State Capitol Building, is hereby reappropriated and redesignated to
16 address the ongoing increased demand for mental health services by
17 purchasing and renovating a replacement facility for Griffin
18 Memorial Hospital; provided, that such facility be confined within a
19 thirty-mile radius of the State Capitol Building and to retain a
20 third-party construction manager with experience in behavioral
21 health hospitals to assist in this project. Such funds shall be
22 utilized in a manner consistent with the recommendations adopted by
23 the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding on May 12, 2025. If,
24 on the date this act is approved, any of the amount originally
SB1178 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 appr opriated, as adjusted by expenditures, encumbrances and
2 transfers, results in an unencumbered balance less than the
3 reappropriated and redesignated amount, that reappropriated and
4 redesignated amount is reduced to the unencumbered amount.
5 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
6 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
7 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
8 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
